# Module 5: Delta Lake

# Topic 36: MERGE (UPSERT) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

## Why?

Suppose:

**Existing Table**

| ID | Name  |
| -- | ----- |
| 1  | Alice |
| 2  | Bob   |

**New File**

| ID | Name    |
| -- | ------- |
| 2  | Bobby   |
| 3  | Charlie |

Expected Result

| ID | Name    |
| -- | ------- |
| 1  | Alice   |
| 2  | Bobby   |
| 3  | Charlie |

You need to **Update existing records + Insert new records**.

---

## Concept

**MERGE** performs **UPDATE + INSERT** in a single command.

> MERGE = UPSERT

---

## Theory

Checks whether a matching record exists.

* Exists → UPDATE
* Doesn't exist → INSERT

---

## Architecture

```text
Source Table
      │
      ▼
    MERGE
      │
      ▼
Target Delta Table
```

---

## Syntax

```sql
MERGE INTO target t
USING source s
ON t.id = s.id

WHEN MATCHED
THEN UPDATE SET *

WHEN NOT MATCHED
THEN INSERT *
```

---

## Real-world Use

* CDC (Change Data Capture)
* Customer Master
* Daily Sales Updates
* Employee Data

---

## Interview Questions

* What is MERGE?
* Difference between INSERT and MERGE?
* What is UPSERT?

---

## ETL Usage

Bronze → Silver Layer

---

## Common Mistake

❌ Using INSERT instead of MERGE for incremental loads.

